Package com.iontrading.mkv

Class MkvFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvObject
      • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvFunction
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrivateMkvFunction
    @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public class MkvFunction
extends MkvObject
    The MkvFunction class wraps a ION Bus Function in a Java Object.

    Functions are asynchronously invokable objects. Call requests to local or remote functions may be done invoking the call method; possibly for each request a response or an error will be notified via the specified MkvFunctionCallListener listener invocation.
    Call requests to locally defined functions are notified via the constructor-specified MkvFunctionListener listener invocations.

    Unless otherwise noted, passing a null argument to a constructor or method in this class will cause a NullPointerException to be thrown.

    See Also:
    MkvFieldType, MkvFunctionCallEvent, MkvFunctionCallListener, MkvFunctionListener

      • call

        public void call​(MkvSupply supply,
                 MkvFunctionCallListener mfl)
          throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,
                 MkvInvalidSupplyException,
                 MkvConnectionException
        Requests a call to this MkvFunction.

        Since the function call is an asynchronous operation, a call to either a local or remote function may produce no effect.
        The parameters are extracted from the specified supply looping from the lower set index up to the higher one and serializing all indexes which are set.

        Many facilities for wrapping java objects into an object with Supply interface can be found in the MkvSupplyFactory class.

        Parameters:
        supply - function parameters.
        mfl - the listener to call on response or on error.
        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotAvailableException - if this function is not available on the Platform.
        MkvConnectionException - if the connection with the publisher of this MkvFunction has been broken.
        MkvInvalidSupplyException - if supply types don't match arguments types.
        See Also:
        MkvSupplyFactory, MkvSupply, MkvFunctionCallListener

                      MkvFunctionCallListener mfl)
               throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,

        Requests a call to this MkvFunction and return its id.

        This works the same as the call method, except that it returns the id for the function call.
        It must be considered that for local function calls this method will return after both the function and the associated listener invocation.

      • call

        public void call​(MkvSupply supply,
                 MkvCallerInfo info,
                 MkvFunctionCallListener mfl)
          throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,
                 MkvInvalidSupplyException,
                 MkvConnectionException
        Requests a call to this MkvFunction, propagating the extended information about the original caller.

        Since the function call is an asynchronous operation, a call to either a local or remote function may produce no effect.
        The parameters are extracted from the specified supply looping from the lower set index up to the higher one and serializing all indexes which are set.

        Many facilities for wrapping java objects into an object with Supply interface can be found in the MkvSupplyFactory class. This method is meant to be used by components which need to forward the information about the original caller to any downstream components. A component can retrieve the information about the original caller using MkvFunctionCallEvent.getCallerInfo(). Example: Suppose component A invokes a function on component B. In order to complete the business action, component B needs to invoke other functions on downstream component C. In such scenario, component B can forward the information about the original caller A, so that component C knows the requests are actually coming on-behalf-of A.

        Parameters:
        supply - function parameters.
        info - the information about the original caller.
        mfl - the listener to call on response or on error.
        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotAvailableException - if this function is not available on the Platform.
        MkvConnectionException - if the connection with the publisher of this MkvFunction has been broken.
        MkvInvalidSupplyException - if supply types don't match arguments types.
        See Also:
        MkvSupplyFactory, MkvSupply, MkvCallerInfo, MkvFunctionCallEvent.getCallerInfo(), MkvFunctionCallListener
